OL,3,CWalsall football kit confusion for
OL,4,Ccolour-blind fans
OL,6,FColour-blind fans watching Walsall's
OL,7,Fmatch against Swindon Town were left
OL,8,Funable to tell the teams apart thanks
OL,9,Fto a clash in the colour of their kits.
OL,11,FWalsall played in an all-black strip
OL,12,Fwhile Swindon wore red.
OL,14,FTo a colour-blind person, both sets of
OL,15,Fplayers seemed to be wearing a near-
OL,16,Fidentical dark-grey kit.
OL,18,FTo most of the 7,786 fans at the game,
OL,19,Fthe teams would have looked perfectly
OL,20,Fnormal, like this:
